X: 27
T: Abide, O Dearest Jesus
T: (SSAATTBB arr. for lever harp accompaniment)
C: Words: Joshua Stegmann, 1628. Translated by August Crull, c. 1892.
C: Music: 'Christus der ist mein Leben', Melchior Vulpius, 1609.
C: Setting: "Mehrstimmiges ChoralBuch", 1906. SSAATTBB arr. Key: Eb major (no transposition).
C: copyright: public domain. Source: Open Hymnal Project, 2013 Revision.
S: Expanded from Open Hymnal SATB. Arranger: Claude Sonnet 4.6, 2026.
M: 4/4
L: 1/4
Q: 1/4=120
%%staves {(V1 V2) (V3 V4) (V5 V6) (V7 V8)}
V:1 name="Soprano I"   clef=treble
V:2 name="Soprano II"  clef=treble
V:3 name="Alto I"      clef=treble
V:4 name="Alto II"     clef=treble
V:5 name="Tenor I"     clef=treble middle=B3 transpose=-12
V:6 name="Tenor II"    clef=treble middle=B3 transpose=-12
V:7 name="Baritone"    clef=bass
V:8 name="Bass I"      clef=bass
K: Eb
%
% ── PHRASE 1 (pickup + bars 1–2) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
% SSAA choir only; TTBB tacet. 4-voice opening texture establishes the melody
% in a chamber-choir sound before the full ensemble enters.
%
% S1 — original soprano, unaltered.
% S2 — diatonic third below S1 throughout phrase 1.
% A1 — independent inner line, Bb3–C4 range; passing tone on beat 4 of bar 1.
% A2 — contrary motion to A1; Eb3–F3 range.
%
[V:1] [Q:1/4=120] E | G F G A | B2 !fermata!G c |
[V:2] C | E D E F | G2 E A |
[V:3] G, | B, G, B, A, | G,2 B, C |
[V:4] E, | G, E, G, F, | G,2 F, E, |
[V:5] z | z4 | z4 |
[V:6] z | z4 | z4 |
[V:7] z | z4 | z4 |
[V:8] z | z4 | z4 |
%
% ── PHRASE 1 cont. (bars 3–4) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
% TTBB choir enters on beat 1 of bar 3 — full 8 voices.
%
% T1 — original tenor (dotted figure mirrors soprano).
% T2 — straight quarters (G3–Eb3) for rhythmic independence against T1.
%   Avoids all T-voice / B-voice pitch unisons (verified beat by beat).
% Bar — entering on Eb3 (unison with B1, deliberate cadential blend);
%   steps to G3–F3–D3, arriving on G3 at bar 4 cadence.
% B1 — original bass with dotted figure at bar 3.
% Bar 4: T1–T2 unison on Bb3 for cadential blend; Bar on G3; B1 on Eb3.
%   TTBB cadence chord: Eb3–G3–Bb3–Bb3 = Eb major, root position.
%
[V:1] B3/2 A/ G F | G2 |
[V:2] G3/2 F/ E D | E2 |
[V:3] G,3/2 A,/ B, G, | B,2 |
[V:4] E,3/2 D,/ E, F, | G,2 |
[V:5] B3/2 A/ B B | B2 |
[V:6] G E G G | G2 |
[V:7] E, G, F, D, | G,2 |
[V:8] E,3/2 F,/ E, B,, | E,2 |
%
% ── PHRASE 2 (pickup + bars 5–6) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
% Antiphonal pickup: TTBB alone on the pickup beat (Bb3/G/G3/Eb3);
%   SSAA re-enters on beat 1 of bar 5. Full 8-voice texture from bar 5.
%
% Bar 5 harmonic sequence: IV (Ab) – vi (Cm) – V (Bb) – I (Eb).
% Bar 6: fermata at climax (S1 C5, B1 Ab2); inner voices sustain.
%   T2 uses F3–F3–Eb3 to avoid T2=B1 pitch unison on beats 3–4.
%   Bar uses C3–Bb3–G2; Bb3 on beat 3 avoids T1–Bar unison (T1=G3).
%
[V:1] z B | c c d e | c2 !fermata!B G |
[V:2] z G | A A B c | A2 G E |
[V:3] z B, | C E D E | E2 B, G, |
[V:4] z E, | G, F, E, F, | E,2 G, F, |
[V:5] z G | A G B B | A2 G B |
[V:6] z E | F E G G | F2 F E |
[V:7] z G, | C, B, D, A,, | C,2 B, G,, |
[V:8] z E, | A,, C, B,, G,, | A,,2 E, E,, |
%
% ── PHRASE 2 cont. (bars 7–8) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
% Call-and-response outer voices: S1 descends (F4–Eb4–Eb4–D4),
%   B1 ascends (F2–G2–Ab2–Bb2) — converging motion frames the final cadence.
% Inner voices provide stepwise harmonic filler:
%   A1: Ab3–G3–Ab3–G3  (neighbor-tone oscillation, converging to G3 at cadence)
%   A2: F3–Eb3–F3–G3   (rising line, contrary to S2)
%   T1: Ab3–G3–F3–F3   (original tenor, stepwise descent)
%   T2: F3–Eb3–D3–D3   (third below T1 throughout)
%   Bar: Ab2–Bb2–C3–Bb2 (arch, ends on Bb2 for open-fifth below B1)
%
% Bar 8 (3-beat final cadence): full 8-voice homophony.
%   Chord: Eb4–C4–Bb3–G3 (SSAA) / G3–Eb3–G2–Eb2 (TTBB).
%   = Eb major with added 6th (C), voiced with B1 on low Eb2.
%   S–A pitch-class unisons: none (verified).
%   T–B pitch-class unisons: none (T1=G3, Bar=G2 — different octaves only).
%
[V:1] F E E D | E3 !eintro!|]
[V:2] D C C B, | C3 |]
[V:3] A, G, A, G, | B,3 |]
[V:4] F, E, F, G, | G,3 |]
[V:5] A G F F | G3 |]
[V:6] F E D D | E3 |]
[V:7] A,, B,, C, B,, | G,,3 |]
[V:8] F,, G,, A,, B,, | E,,3 |]
